
Fri Sep  6 11:44:29 PDT 2002

This dir contains original Matlab functions from the ICA/EEG (now EEGLAB) Matlab toolbox,
plus many new EEGLAB v4.0 functions. See the EEGLAB tutorial (URL given below).

To use: 

1. Place the matlab functions in a directory ($DIR) and add 
   $DIR/eeglab4.0 to (Unix) your matlabpath environment variable. 
   Else, in Matlab >> addpath('full_path_here')

2. Edit file "icadefs.m" to reference the faster binary "ica" function. 
   This requires a (recommended) separate download from http://sccn.ucsd.edu/eeglab/binica/
   Also add the path for the EEGLAB tutorial. This requires another (recommended) download 
   from http://sccn.ucsd.edu/eeglab/

3. Start Matlab. and type >> eeglab

4. Open the main EEGLAB tutorial page (your downloaded eeglabtut.html 
   else http://sccn.ucsd.edu/eeglab/eeglabtut.html)

5. Please send feedback and suggestions to eeglab@sccn.ucsd.edu

6. In publications, please reference:

   A. Delorme, S. Makeig et al., "EEGLAB: A software toolbox for electrophysiological data 
   analysis" WWW release: http://sccn.ucsd.edu/eeglab/, Version 4.0 The Salk Institute, 
   La Jolla and Swartz Center for Computational Neuroscience, Institute for Neural Computation, 
   University of California San Diego, September, 2002
 

Arno Delorme & Scott Makeig
